South Korea Stocks: Hynix, Kolon Industries, Shinhan Financial

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-09-15T07:11:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/south-korea-stocks-hynix-kolon-industries-samsung-electronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. close in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  rose 1.4 percent to 1,774.08, halting a
two-day, 5.3 percent retreat.  Banks: Shinhan Financial Group Co. (055550 KS) lost 4.4
percent to 38,450 won.  Hana Financial Group Inc. (086790)  (086790 KS)
retreated 2 percent to 32,650 won.  KB Financial Group Inc. (105560) 
(105560 KS) sank 2 percent to 36,500 won. The nation’s financial
watchdog plans to make lenders beef up foreign-currency holdings
as several failed stricter stress tests, Yonhap News reported .  South Korea’s financial regulator last month completed
stress tests on local banks’ foreign-currency liquidity, Ernst Lee, a spokesman for the Financial Services Commission, said by
phone, declining to elaborate further on the report.  Hynix Semiconductor Inc. (000660)  (000660 KS), the world’s second-
largest computer-memory chipmaker, climbed 6.3 percent to 21,100
won, the highest close since Aug. 11. The stock advanced on
speculation prices of computer memory chips will stabilize soon,
said Choi Do Yeon, an analyst with LIG Investment & Securities
Co. Hynix’s bigger rival Samsung Electronics Co. (005930 KS)
added 2.4 percent to 771,000 won.  Kolon Industries Inc. (120110)  (120110 KS) tumbled by the daily
limit of 15 percent to 76,100 won, the lowest level since April
6. DuPont Co. won a $919.9 million jury award from Kolon over
the theft of  trade secrets  about the manufacture of Kevlar, an
anti-ballistic fiber used in police and military gear.  Kolon
Corp. (002020)  (002020 KS), Kolon Industries’ biggest shareholder, also
dropped 15 percent to 25,050 won.  SK Broadband Co. (033630 KS), an  Internet service provider ,
gained 0.9 percent to 3,390 won.  Fitch Ratings  upgraded SK
Broadband’s long-term foreign- and local-currency issuer default
ratings and its senior unsecured debt rating to A- from BBB+.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
